She is grazing in Sila’s great forest, a lovely heifer: the bulls in alternate onset join battle with mighty force3 many a wound they deal, black gore bathes their frames, amid mighty bellowing the levelled horns are driven against the butting foe3 the woods and the sky, from end to end, re-echo. Nor is it the r1vals’ wont to herd together, but the vanquished one departs, and dwells an exile in unknown soenes afar. Much does he bewail his shame, and the blows of his haughty conqueror, and much the love he has lost unavenged —then‚ with a wistful glance at his stall, he has quitted his ancestral realm. Therefore with all heed he trains his powers, and on an unstrewn couch, among flinty rocks, lies through the night, with prickly leaves and pointed sedge for fare. Anon he tests himself, and, learning to throw wrath into his horns, charges a tree's trunk3 he lashes the winds with blows, and paws the sand in prelude for the fray. Soon, when his power is mustered and his strength renewed, he advances the colours, and dashes head- long on his unmindful foe: as, when a ware begins to whiten in mid-sea, from the farther deep it arches its curve, and, rolling shoreward, roars thundering along the reefs, and, huge as a very mountain, falls prone, while from below the water boils up in eddies, and tosses black sand alost.
